history.content:
I'm taking EE127 right now with Math 54 + Math 110 (I have not taken EE16a/b) and found it perfectly feasible. 

Once in a while they have mentioned an example/application covered in 16a/b not in 54/110 but I manage just fine. 

I might not 100% recommend 127 with only 54 experience due to 54 being pretty computational and 127 on the level of abstract linear algebra proofs. 

My semesters of 54 + 110 didn't stress some topics like PSD matrices and SVD, but the first third of 127 goes over that (this is one of the reasons I am really enjoying the course because I'm doing something I love (linear algebra) but still learning new material).

Additionally, this semester there was a diagnostic quiz on the 2nd lecture to make sure you had enough lin alg experience and I felt it was perfectly fine with 54 + 110.
Given linear algebra experience (Math54/110) would it be feasible to do EECS127 next semester, or is the material from EE16A/B very pertinent to the class
history.subject: How important is EE16A/B for EECS127?
